Male and Female Customers are equally satisfied. There are more Loyal Customers than disloyal ones, and the loyal ones are more satisfied, however both groups are more neutral or dissatisfied than satisfied. More customers travel for business and they are more satisfied than the ones who travel for personal reasons. Most of the Customers travel Business and Economy class, but customers who chose Business are a lot more satisfied.

df_num_norm=(df_num-df_num.mean())/df_num.std()
# Compute the correlation matrix
corr = df_num_norm.corr()
# Generate a mask for the upper triangle
mask = np.triu(np.ones_like(corr, dtype=bool))

plt.figure(figsize=(20,20))
sns.heatmap(corr, mask=mask,vmin=-.8,vmax=0.8,annot=True)

In[36]:
#normalize data
df_ratings=df[['Inflight wifi service',
       'Departure/Arrival time convenient', 'Ease of Online booking',
       'Gate location', 'Food and drink', 'Online boarding', 'Seat comfort',
       'Inflight entertainment', 'On-board service', 'Leg room service',
       'Baggage handling', 'Checkin service', 'Inflight service',
       'Cleanliness', 'satisfied']]
df_rat_norm=(df_ratings-df_ratings.mean())/df_ratings.std()
# Compute the correlation matrix
corr = df_rat_norm.corr()
# Generate a mask for the upper triangle
mask = np.triu(np.ones_like(corr, dtype=bool))

plt.figure(figsize=(20,20))
sns.heatmap(corr, mask=mask,vmin=-.8,vmax=0.8,annot=True)

       'Departure/Arrival time convenient', 'Ease of Online booking',
       'Gate location', 'Food and drink', 'Online boarding', 'Seat comfort',
       'Inflight entertainment', 'On-board service', 'Leg room service',

In[42]:
import scipy
##create regplot
p = sns.regplot(data=df_num, x='Arrival Delay in Minutes', y='Departure Delay in Minutes')

#calculate slope and intercept of regression equation
slope, intercept, r, p, sterr = scipy.stats.linregress(x=p.get_lines()[0].get_xdata(),
                                                       y=p.get_lines()[0].get_ydata())

#add regression equation to plot
plt.text(5, 1400, 'y = ' + str(round(intercept,3)) + ' + ' + str(round(slope,3)) + 'x')
Out[42]:
Text(5, 1400, 'y = 0.314 + 0.951x')
